# Goal: Building the Native Virtual Browser Remote Login UI

The objective is to expose a UI that allows a user to "VNC" directly into the Autopilot Agent's headless Playwright browser running on the Cloud VM. By manually logging in once through this interface, Google generates native, device-bound, encrypted credentials directly on the VM's hardware. This acts as a 100% perfect browser profile clone that is immune to Google's anti-bot measures and cookie-sync limitations.

> [!NOTE]
> The backend endpoints for this functionality already exist in `apps/runner/src/server.ts`. This implementation plan focuses purely on building the missing Frontend interface to consume them. 

## Proposed Changes

### apps/demo-web

We will introduce a new "Remote Login Viewer" component to the frontend application that continuously fetches screenshots from the VM and translates user inputs into browser commands.

#### [NEW] `apps/demo-web/src/components/RemoteLoginViewer.tsx`
This will be the core interactive component.
- **Image Polling**: Runs a `setInterval` or recursive `requestAnimationFrame` loop to fetch `GET /api/browser/login-screenshot` every ~300ms.
- **Click Handling**: Listens for `onClick` events on the image. It will calculate the relative `(x, y)` coordinates based on the image's original dimensions vs its rendered display size, and transmit them via `POST /api/browser/login-click`.
- **Keyboard Handling**: Captures a global or focused `onKeyDown` listener. Maps special keys (Enter, Backspace, Tab, Arrows) to `POST /api/browser/login-keypress`, and groups textual characters to `POST /api/browser/login-type`.

#### [MODIFY] `apps/demo-web/src/app/page.tsx` (or primary dashboard layout)
- Add a button: "Launch Remote Setup / Sync Profile".
- Clicking this triggers `POST /api/browser/login-start` with the desired profile name and standard Google login URL.
- Mounts the `RemoteLoginViewer.tsx` component in a modal or dedicated pane.
- Add a "Close Session & Save Profile" button that calls `POST /api/browser/login-close`, fully saving the SQLite profile back to the disk.

## Security & Reliability Considerations

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Because you are interacting with a Headless Chromium/Chrome instance natively, ensure that your `.env` contains `CUA_BROWSER_CHANNEL="chrome"` for the best stealth masking.

> [!TIP]
> Since clicking relies on `x, y` mapping, ensure the UI does not stretch or distort the aspect ratio of the 1280x800 raw image returned by the server, otherwise clicks will miss their targets.

## Open Questions

1. **Frontend Repository**: Does your frontend currently reside in `apps/demo-web` or is this going into your connected `landing-app`/`admin-panel` application (e.g. `insocialWISE/landing-app`)? 
2. **Authentication**: Do the `/api/browser/login-*` endpoints currently require any JWT validation, or does the runner handle auth via standard CORS? 

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1. Launch the new UI in the frontend. 
2. Click "Launch Remote Setup". Verify the modal appears and the Google Login screen renders visually on your machine.
3. Type an email, click the "Next" button in the image feed, and verify the password screen renders.
4. Finalize login, verify 2FA succeeds, and click "Close Session". 
5. Run the actual Agent Prompt directly against Google Drive to confirm the session persists organically without throwing "Choose an Account."
